<subSubSection id="C4F1E4857038FFE2FF6CFD92036C142F" pageId="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8C54B70E7038FFE2FF6CFD92036C142F" blockId="6.[151,639,194,1172]" pageId="6">
<emphasis id="BE9F6B1C7038FFE2FF6CFD9200611556" bold="true" box="[175,275,513,534]" pageId="6">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4BEBCC8D7038FFE2FEE3FD93008C1555" authorityName="Prathapan and Konstantinov" authorityYear="2011" box="[288,510,512,533]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aphthona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yercaudensis">
<emphasis id="BE9F6B1C7038FFE2FEE3FD93008C1555" box="[288,510,512,533]" italics="true" pageId="6">Aphthona yercaudensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated easily from 
<taxonomicName id="4BEBCC8D7038FFE2FE96FD8800871570" box="[341,501,539,560]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aphthona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombayensis">
<emphasis id="BE9F6B1C7038FFE2FE96FD8800871570" box="[341,501,539,560]" italics="true" pageId="6">A. bombayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by: its light yellow-brown color (general color of 
<taxonomicName id="4BEBCC8D7038FFE2FE2EFDA6030C150A" box="[493,638,565,586]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aphthona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombayensis">
<emphasis id="BE9F6B1C7038FFE2FE2EFDA6030C150A" box="[493,638,565,586]" italics="true" pageId="6">A. bombayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is dark brown); a sharp frontal ridge (the frontal ridge is comparatively broader in 
<taxonomicName id="4BEBCC8D7038FFE2FE18FDF8031D15C0" box="[475,623,619,640]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aphthona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombayensis">
<emphasis id="BE9F6B1C7038FFE2FE18FDF8031D15C0" box="[475,623,619,640]" italics="true" pageId="6">A. bombayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); three pairs of well-developed labral setae (only two pairs of labral setae are well-developed in 
<taxonomicName id="4BEBCC8D7038FFE2FF54FD29004A158F" box="[151,312,698,719]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aphthona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombayensis">
<emphasis id="BE9F6B1C7038FFE2FF54FD29004A158F" box="[151,312,698,719]" italics="true" pageId="6">A. bombayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the median lobe of aedeagus widest near middle in ventral view (median lobe of aedeagus widest proximal to middle in ventral view in 
<taxonomicName id="4BEBCC8D7038FFE2FF2BFC99000F145F" box="[232,381,778,799]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aphthona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombayensis">
<emphasis id="BE9F6B1C7038FFE2FF2BFC99000F145F" box="[232,381,778,799]" italics="true" pageId="6">A. bombayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<figureCitation id="14D0AB8B7038FFE2FE4EFC9900B7145F" box="[397,453,778,799]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[197,237,1686,1705]" captionTargetBox="[177,1190,1119,1662]" captionTargetId="figure-403@3.[174,1191,1116,1663]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Aphthona bombayensis. 1) Median lobe of aedeagus, ventral view; 2) Median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 3) Median lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view; 4) Spermatheca; 5) Vaginal palpi; 6) Tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5340697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5340697/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); and the shape of the spermatheca. Adults were collected while flying and landing on broad leaves of a shrub, performing a characteristic display in bright daylight.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
